CatDescriptText: Miss Audrey Dixon, 2405 Bedford Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 25, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that business and employment are as good as the Eisenhower administration declares that it is?" answer reads: "No, and the reason I say this is because people are out of work and it is hard to find a job anywhere. For ..... teachers are not being paid good wages, the schools are overlooked and there are not enough teachers.
